Cut the @red onions{3} in half through the root, remove the skin and finely chop. Put @olive oil{2 1/2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on very low heat, and add the onions and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Leave to slowly caramelise for ~{25%minutes}, stirring occasionally, ensuring they don't burn. Add the @honey{1.5%tbsp} at the end and cook for a further ~{3-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mix the @yeast{1%packet} with @warm water{200%ml} and a @sugar{pinch} (if you have it). Put @flour{300%g} in a #big mixing bowl{} and stir in @salt{1%tsp}. Make a well in the middle of the flour big enough to hold the yeast mixture.

Tip the yeast mixture and @olive oil{1%tbsp} into the well, then slowly start moving the flour in from the sides and mixing it with the liquid. Keep moving the flour into the liquid and mixing thoroughly, until you have a nice squidgy ball of dough.

Place the dough on a floured work surface and knead it for ~{5%minutes} (at least!). > Kneading simply means stretching the dough to make it nice and springy. Hold down the end of the dough nearest to you with one hand and use the palm of your other hand to push the rest of the dough away from you in a long stretching motion. Fold it in half and repeat...you're now kneading!

Once the dough is ready, leave it in a #bowl{} in a warm place for at least ~{15%minutes} to prove. > For best results, you can leave it a little longer!

Meanwhile, pre-heat your #oven{} to its maximum temperature and put two lightly oiled #baking trays{} in the oven, with a large piece of #tin foil{} on each, ready for the pizza bases. Roughly chop the @goat's cheese{1/2}.

== Toppings ==

Pick the @oregano{3%sprigs} leaves.

== Assembly and Baking ==

When the pizza dough is ready, dust the work surface with the remaining @flour{50%g}, divide the dough into two balls and roll them out on the floured surface, until nice and thin - roughly 25cm across. > If you don't have a rolling pin you can always use a wine bottle (or even a tin can at a push!).

Spread the @tomato puree{4%tbsp} thinly over each pizza base. Divide the caramelised onions between each pizza base and top with the oregano and as much goat's cheese as you like!

Pop both pizza bases on top of the lightly oiled pre-heated baking trays, on the top shelf of the oven, for ~{8-10%minutes}. Once cooked, top with a handful of @wild rocket{1%handful} and a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Job done!